history.content:
The best way for you to get an early start is to look at the course materials here: https://cs61a.org 

DeNero is teaching the class again Fall 2018, and the course materials don't change very much between semesters.

Hello, everyone,

I am a freshman who is an intended applied math and econ major, but also want to try minor in data science. So next semester, I would like to learn CS 61A. For programming, I have learned data 8(feel good)and AP CS in high school(but not so well).What resources do you recommend to use in the summer time to get early start so that won't be too stressed out next semester? Any advice is appreciated. Thanks!
